        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Neuschwanstein Castle Viewpoints</h2>
        <p>A large network of trails through the forest-covered hills and mountains exists around Neuschwanstein Castle for tourists to explore. Many of the iconic views overlooking Neuschwanstein Castle amongst the beautiful Bavarian landscape can be found along these trails. Just below the castle is the <strong>Skywalk Neuschwanstein</strong>, providing close-up views of the castle.</p>
        <p>Continue up to the <strong>Panoramablick Schwangau</strong> to admire the backside of the castle rising up out of the forest. This viewpoint is next to the <strong>Hohenschwangau Viewpoint</strong>, which is named for its amazing views overlooking the Hohenschwangau Castle rising above the village below.</p>
        <h3>Marienbr&#252;cke Bridge</h3>
        <p>A bit further up the mountain is the <strong>Marienbr&#252;cke Bridge</strong>, which spans over a gorge and the beautiful <strong>P&#246;llat Waterfall</strong>. From this bridge you can enjoy the most iconic view of Neuschwanstein Castle, with its long side rising up above the forests, framed against the rural landscape behind it.</p>
        <h3>Mountain Views</h3>
        <p>Continue even further up the mountain to the <strong>Neuschwanstein Viewpoint</strong>, from which you can admire the Marienbr&#252;cke bridge with the castle seen behind it. This viewpoint is only about 12 minutes up the mountain from Neuschwanstein, and beyond this are many more hiking trails providing alternate viewpoints and different perspectives overlooking the castle.</p>
    </section>



